Plain-English summary (non-binding, the formal clauses below govern):

  You may use EbonClearance freely, including on private servers and in
  addon-pack bundles. You may modify it and share your modifications. You
  may not quietly rebrand it as your own work: the credits, the in-game
  byline, the provenance globals, the LICENSE file, and the SavedVariable
  / slash-command / import-export identifiers must stay intact. Forking
  under a new name with full attribution preserved is fine; copying it,
  renaming it, and presenting it as an original work is not. There is no
  warranty.

  Note on prior art: this licence's structure and the
  `__<addon>_origin` / `__<addon>_author` provenance-globals form
  follow patterns that exist elsewhere in the WoW 3.3.5a addon
  ecosystem. EbonClearance adopted these patterns rather than
  claiming originality; see NOTICE.md for the acknowledgement.

Formal terms:

1. Grant of Rights
   Subject to the conditions in sections 2-3, the copyright holder grants
   every recipient a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, irrevocable
   (except as provided in section 6) licence to use, reproduce, modify,
   distribute, and redistribute this Software, in source or compiled form,
   for any lawful purpose.

2. Attribution Preservation
   Any redistribution of the Software, whether modified or unmodified,
   whether source or compiled, must preserve each of the following without
   alteration:

   (a) the "## Author:" line in the addon's .toc manifest;
   (b) the comment block at the top of the primary Lua source file naming
       the author and the canonical source URL;
   (c) the "by <author>  ·  <url>" byline rendered on the main options
       panel of the in-game settings UI;
   (d) the global variables EBONCLEARANCE_IDENT, EBONCLEARANCE_AUTHOR,
       EBONCLEARANCE_ORIGIN, __EbonClearance_origin,
       __EbonClearance_author, and __EbonClearance_watermark, along
       with the values they carry;
   (e) this LICENSE file, in full, in every distributed copy.

   Attribution must be genuine. Replacing the author name, URL, or
   provenance values with placeholder, empty, or misleading content
   constitutes a breach of this section.

3. No Silent Rebrand
   The following identifiers may not be renamed in any derivative work
   without the prior written permission of the copyright holder:

   (a) the visible addon name "EbonClearance";
   (b) the slash command "/ec";
   (c) the SavedVariable table names "EbonClearanceDB" and
       "EbonClearanceAccountDB";
   (d) the import/export string prefix "EC:".

   You may fork the Software under a different name provided that
   sections 2 and 3(a)-(d) are honoured in full, the fork makes its
   derivative nature explicit, and a link back to the canonical source
   is preserved alongside the attribution required by section 2. Covertly
   renaming any of the identifiers in (a)-(d) to obscure the origin of
   the Software is a breach of this section.

4. Addon-Pack Bundling
   Unmodified copies of the Software may be included in private-server
   addon-pack distributions without seeking individual permission,
   provided section 2 is honoured in full. Modifications or partial
   inclusion (e.g. extracting a single file) require the same attribution
   preservation as any other redistribution.

5. No Warranty
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS
   OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF
   MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NONINFRINGEMENT.
   IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY
   CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT,
   TORT, OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE
   SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.

6. Termination
   The rights granted in section 1 terminate automatically upon any
   breach of section 2 or section 3. Compliance with those sections must
   be restored within thirty (30) days of notice for the rights to be
   reinstated.

7. Severability
   If any provision of this licence is found unenforceable, the remaining
   provisions remain in force.
